      • GameLogic

        public GameLogic(Dimension size,
                 boolean aiOpponent,
                 AIDifficulty aiDifficulty)
        Another constructor for class TicTacToeGame. Creates a new object of type TicTacToeGame with the given size containing rows and column counts for the games territory.
        Parameters:
        size - the size of the tic tac toe game territory
        aiOpponent - whether this game is a game against an AI player
        aiDifficulty - the AI difficulty for this game

    • Method Detail

      • makeHumanPlayerMove

        public void makeHumanPlayerMove()
        Lets a human player make a move. Lets a human player make a move by first verifying that it's the human players turn and then letting the current human player whose turn it is make a move.

      • endMove

        public void endMove()
        Ends a players move. Ends a players move by checking if the game should now end (checkEnd()) and if not, setting the next player whose turn it is (setNextPlayer()) and then checking if its currently the AI player's turn and if yes, letting it make its move (checkAIPlayersTurn()).

      • isHumanPlayersTurn

        public boolean isHumanPlayersTurn()
        Gets whether its currently the human player's turn. Gets whether its the human player's turn by checking if the current player to mark a tile is not an AI player.
        Returns:
        true if its the human players turn, otherwise false

      • isInGame

        public boolean isInGame()
        Gets if the game is ingame. Gets if the game is ingame by checking if the games state getGameState() is GameState.INGAME.
        Returns:
        true if this tic tac toe game is still ingame, otherwise returns false

      • isEnded

        public boolean isEnded()
        Gets if the game ended. Gets if the game ended by checking if the games state getGameState() is not GameState.INGAME.
        Returns:
        true if this tic tac toe game ended already, otherwise returns false

      • isDraw

        public boolean isDraw()
        Gets if the game ended with a draw. Gets if the game ended with a draw by checking if the games state getGameState() is GameState.DRAW.
        Returns:
        true if this tic tac toe game ended with a draw, in all other cases returns false

      • isPlayingAgainstAI

        public boolean isPlayingAgainstAI()
        Gets if the player is playing against AI. Gets if the human player is playing against an AI opponent by checking if the count of AI players in the list in the instance variable players is greater than zero.
        Returns:
        true if opponent is AI, otherwise false

      • getSize

        public Dimension getSize()
        Gets the size. Returns the size of this tic tac toe game representing the rows and columns counts of its square territory.
        Returns:
        the size of this territory

      • getTerritory

        public Territory getTerritory()
        Gets the games territory. Returns the territory object for this tic tac toe game.
        Returns:
        the territory of this tic tac toe game

      • getPlayers

        public java.util.List<Player> getPlayers()
        Gets the games players set. Returns a set of player objects for this tic tac toe game.
        Returns:
        the players of this tic tac toe game

      • getGameState

        public GameState getGameState()
        Gets the games state. Returns the value of the instance variable gameState. Possible values for the game state are INGAME, DRAW and WON.
        Returns:
        the state of this tic tac toe game.

      • getWinner

        public Player getWinner()
        Gets the games winner. Returns the value of the instance variable winner containing null or a reference to a player who won this tic tac toe game.
        Returns:
        the winner of this tic tac toe game (null if not won yet).
